Git command..............

To connect local machine to git 

---> git config --global user.email "yourEmailID"

To add git repo 

---> git remote add origin <git repo url>

To fetch all the changes made in git repo

---> git fetch --all

To check remote repo 

---> git remote -v

Rename or Update the Existing Remote:

---> git remote set-url origin https://new-url-to-repository

To remove 

---> git remote remove origin

After removing the remote, you can add the new one using:

---> git remote add origin https://github.com/Dhiraj111/DemoGIT.git

Remove Local Repository:

---> rm -rf your-repo-name

To delete remote branch 

---> git push origin --delete branch-name

Check Remote Branches:

---> git branch -r

###########################################################################

how to merge to branches e.g demo to main 

---> git fetch origin
     git checkout main
     git pull origin main
     git merge demo
     git push origin main




